        <abstract>
            <p>"Sambaquis", or shell mounds accumulated by former inhabitants of the coast, contain shells of some animals that FM has never seen living.</p> 
<p>Ants that live on <hi rend="italic">imbauba</hi> trees (<hi rend="italic">Cecropia</hi>) are attracted by small bodies at base of each petiole.</p> 
        </abstract>
